    <!-- What is Mechanical Engineering Section -->
    <section class="section" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">What is Mechanical Engineering?</h2>
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Mechanical engineering is one of the oldest and broadest engineering disciplines. It combines principles of physics and materials science for the design, analysis, manufacturing, and maintenance of mechanical systems.</p>
                    <p>Mechanical engineers design and build everything from small individual parts and devices to large systems and machines. They are involved in various stages of product development, from research and design to installation and final commissioning.</p>
                    <p>As a mechanical engineer, you'll be at the forefront of innovation, creating solutions that address global challenges in energy, transportation, healthcare, and manufacturing.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Specializations Section -->
    <section class="section bg-light" id="specializations">
      <div class="container">
          <h2 class="section-title">Specializations</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">Explore different specializations within mechanical engineering that align with your interests and career goals:</p>
          
