            <div class="faq-container">
                <div class="accordion">
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <div class="accordion-header">What is the difference between Mechanical and Automobile Engineering?</div>
                        <div class="accordion-content">
                            <p>Mechanical Engineering is a broader field that covers the design, manufacturing, and maintenance of mechanical systems in general. Automobile Engineering is a specialized branch that focuses specifically on the design, development, and manufacturing of vehicles. Mechanical engineers can work in various industries, while automobile engineers primarily work in the automotive sector.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <div class="accordion-header">Is coding knowledge necessary for Mechanical Engineers?</div>
                        <div class="accordion-content">
                            <p>While not mandatory, coding knowledge is increasingly valuable for mechanical engineers. Programming skills in languages like MATLAB, Python, and C++ help in automation, simulation, data analysis, and working with CAD/CAM software. As industries embrace Industry 4.0 and smart manufacturing, mechanical engineers with programming skills have a competitive advantage.</p>
